. Three years later, he was wandering again when he passed through the wilds of Song and once more happened upon Hong Meng. Cloud General rejoiced greatly, hastened forward, and said: “Has heaven forgotten me? Has heaven forgotten me?” He bowed twice, touching his head to the ground, and wished to hear Hong Meng’s teaching.

Hong Meng said: “Drifting without aim, knowing not what is sought;
Rampant without direction, knowing not where to go;
Restless and distracted, observing what is not false.”
